Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes #348
Publisher:  DC Comics
Publication Date:  June 1987

Writer:  Paul Levitz and Steve Lightle
Pencillers:  Steve Lightle and Greg LaRocque
Inkers:  Mike DeCarlo
Colorists:  Carl Gafford
Letterer:  John Costanza
Cover:  Steven Lightle and Anthony Tollin

Mon-El is dealing with the reality of Brainiac 5's serum, the serum that temporarily cures his lead poisoning, failing to work anymore. He's gained an immunity to the serum and he may die or be forced to enter the Phantom Zone again. Unfortunately, it's crunch time and Mon-El is forced into the Phantom Zone for his own health, but he resents being there. Element Lad and Brainiac 5 realize that they need to find a cure immediately or they will lose Mon-El forever. While Brainiac 5 rushes for a lasting antidote, Phantom Girl and Tellus enter the Phantom Zone to calm Mon-El down. Meanwhile, a group of Legionnaires travel to the past, to get the aid of Superboy in handling Mon-El. Taking some of Superboy's blood, Brainiac 5 is able to come up with a permanent cure for Mon-El's predicament.

